"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-05-olympic-cyclist-forced-dash-rowdy-pub-toilet-break-mid-race-21363848\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Punters in a packedParispub went wild as they were joined by cyclist Nils Politt in the middle of the men's road race as theOlympianpopped in for a toilet stop.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 69, \"end\": 73, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nils_Granfelt\", \"score\": 0.9586206450290599, \"rank\": 0.04079707049184306, \"text\": \"Nils\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nils_Granfelt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nils_Granfelt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheGermanrider revealed after the event that he was struggling with an upset stomach and he was forced to dash into the famous Cafe des 2 Moulin in Montmartre.\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 0.9999990863627398, \"rank\": 9.136379916935379e-07, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A remarkable video of the moment sees the cyclist being led through the busy bar, past drinkers with beers in hand.\", \"from\": 323, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd obviously loved being up close and personal with the athlete as he returned to his bike and cycled off.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  Politt was not loving life so much, explaining the nightmare situation he found himself in.\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Did not count how much time it took me,' Politt said,' viaFox Sports.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was really warm, we were drinking a lot of water, ate a lot of gels and normally I do not have problems.\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But today I had an upset stomach.'\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"La D\\u00e9p\\u00eache du Midi journalist Arthur Tirat posted the video with the superb piece of French: 'Pause pipi'.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 938, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9p\\u00eache_du_Midi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La D\\u00e9p\\u00eache du Midi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9p\\u00eache_du_Midi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9p\\u00eache_du_Midi\"}, {\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"score\": 0.989060549922614, \"rank\": 0.011060445266109258, \"text\": \"Arthur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/King_Arthur\"}, {\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9841424904274273, \"rank\": 0.00877238072615932, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pause pipi au c\\u00c3\\u00a9l\\u00c3\\u00a8bre Caf\\u00c3\\u00a9 des 2 Moulins pour Nils Politt#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/ybTxqwJqqB  Politt had looked in good shape early on in the road race, but tailed off and finished 70th, certainly not helped by his unexpected visit to the boozer.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgium's Remco Evenepoel claimed gold, with the French pair of Valentin Madouas and Christophe Laporte taking silver and bronze respectively.\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8940401920391323, \"rank\": 0.11851430721284922, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9841424904274273, \"rank\": 0.00877238072615932, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's gold medal hero from the men's cross-country mountain biking, Tom Pidcock, was also in action, finishing 13th.\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7733141829753354, \"rank\": 0.29313266307904673, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I did not have that extra punch.\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was a bit sluggish and slow, and so I was never really in the proper race,' said Pidcock.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Coming out of the mountain biking, I did not want any pressure on this race.\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I said I would go on the calls and talk about it, but my focus was mountain biking.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be honest, my expectations were to be in the race and if I'd got a medal that would be awesome.'\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:BBC commentator orders Olympic judges to intervene after 'frightening' dive  ArrowMORE:Chinese gymnast's priceless reaction as rivals bite their Olympic medals on podium  ArrowMORE:Olympian breaks her own world record twice within a few minutes  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9728403062533875, \"rank\": 0.019484